explanations.reason: The paper focuses on analyzing co-patenting activities in the automotive industry, specifically examining the differences in innovation output based on the type of R&D partners (allies, suppliers, and subsidiaries). The methodology involves descriptive and regression analysis using matched data from co-assigned patent portfolios and relationship types. There is no mention or implication of any machine learning techniques, algorithms, or models in the research. Therefore, none of the provided keywords related to machine learning or its subfields are relevant to this paper.
